tags: Anatomy
title: TW Fields
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The built-in TiddlyWiki fields go here.  Conventionally that means `title`, `tags`, `text`, `type`, `created`, `modified`, `creator`, `modifier`.  Each maps to a binding (see [[Bindings]]) producing the value written to that field on each resulting tiddler.

Typical bindings:

* `"title": "{{author}}: {{title}}"` -- a title built from two source fields.
* `"tags": "Book {{genre|split-commas}}"` -- a static word plus a list-formatted source value.
* `"created": "{{created_at|iso-to-date}}"` -- an ISO timestamp converted to TiddlyWiki's `YYYYMMDDhhmmssXXX` format.

You don't have to bind every built-in field.  Anything you skip is left unset on the resulting tiddler.
